               <p>Bever's Defence. Upon the Wednesday morning, that new hat was brought to me by 
               <persName id="t18151025-108-person904">
                  George 
                  Conner
               <interp inst="t18151025-108-person904" type="surname" value="Conner"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18151025-108-person904" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18151025-108-person904" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , he left it at my lodgings between eight and nine in the morning.</p>
               <p>COURT. How came you to say you bought it. -</p>
               <p>Smedley's Defence. I have got nothing to say, but that I was not in the party. I never saw the burnishing stones, nor that young man, who says I pawned them at his house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18151025-108-person905">
